This morning in Saratskiy district the driver of a "Peugeot" drove onto the oncoming lane at 115 km of the Odessa-Reni highway and collided with a bus carrying six people.
This is being reported by the press office of the Road Emergency Service Administration in the Odessa region.
As a result of the incident, the 31-year-old driver of the "Peugeot" died.
Injured were a 55-year-old passenger and a 44-year-old bus driver, whose leg was jammed.
Medical personnel rendered first aid to the woman on the spot, she declined hospitalization.
Emergency medical personnel also examined all remaining passengers.
Rescuers lifted the bus with the aid of a crane and freed the bus driver whose leg was jammed in the door of the bus.
